# React Component Patterns

## Component Size Limits

**Keep components under 200 lines.** If exceeded, decompose using:

1. **Extract hooks** - Business logic → `use[Name].ts`
2. **Extract subcomponents** - Sections → `[Name]Section.tsx`
3. **Extract renders** - Complex JSX → `render[Name]()`
4. **Extract config** - Constants → `[name].config.ts`

## Component Structure Template

```tsx
// 1. Imports (grouped: react, external, internal, types)
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { Button, Form } from "antd";
import { useDataset } from "../hooks/useDataset";
import type { Dataset } from "../types/dataset";

// 2. Types (interfaces for props)
interface MyComponentProps {
  datasetId: number;
  onComplete?: (result: Dataset) => void;
}

// 3. Component (max 200 lines total)
export function MyComponent({ datasetId, onComplete }: MyComponentProps) {
  // a. Hooks (in order: context, query, state, effects, callbacks)
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useDataset(datasetId);
  const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    // Effects with cleanup
    return () => cleanup();
  }, []);

  // b. Early returns for loading/error states
  if (isLoading) return <Spin />;
  if (error) return <Alert type="error" message={error.message} />;
  if (!data) return null;

  // c. Render (extract to subcomponents if complex)
  return (
    <div>
      <Header data={data} />
      <Content data={data} isEditing={isEditing} />
      <Actions onEdit={() => setIsEditing(true)} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## State Management Patterns

### Local State (useState)

Use for:

- UI state (modals, tabs, editing mode)
- Form input values (if not using Ant Design Form)
- Temporary flags

```tsx
const [isModalOpen, setModalOpen] = useState(false);
const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState("details");
```

### Server State (React Query)

**Always use for:**

- Data from Supabase
- API responses
- Real-time subscriptions

```tsx
// ✅ Correct: Use custom hook
const { data, isLoading, error } = useDatasets();

// ❌ Wrong: Fetch in useEffect
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/datasets").then(/* ... */);
}, []);
```

### Global State (Context)

**Minimize use.** Only for:

- Auth session
- Map viewport sync (specific cases)
- Theme preferences

```tsx
// Context pattern (only when necessary)
const MyContext = createContext<MyContextType | undefined>(undefined);

export function MyProvider({ children }) {
  const value = useMemo(
    () => ({
      /* state */
    }),
    [
      /* deps */
    ],
  );
  return <MyContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</MyContext.Provider>;
}

export function useMyContext() {
  const context = useContext(MyContext);
  if (!context) throw new Error("useMyContext must be within MyProvider");
  return context;
}
```

## Processing Status Patterns

**Centralize status logic** in `src/utils/processingSteps.ts`:

```tsx
import { calculateProcessingProgress } from "../utils/processingSteps";

function DatasetStatus({ dataset }: { dataset: Dataset }) {
  const { isComplete, percentage, currentStepInfo } = calculateProcessingProgress(dataset);

  if (dataset.has_error) return <Tag color="error">Error</Tag>;
  if (isComplete) return <Tag color="success">Complete</Tag>;

  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <Progress percent={percentage} size="small" />
      <span>{currentStepInfo.label}</span>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Form Patterns

### Ant Design Forms (Preferred)

```tsx
function MyForm({ onSubmit }: { onSubmit: (values: FormValues) => void }) {
  const [form] = Form.useForm();

  // Watch for reactive validation
  const name = Form.useWatch("name", form);
  const isValid = name && name.length > 3;

  return (
    <Form form={form} onFinish={onSubmit} layout="vertical">
      <Form.Item label="Name" name="name" rules={[{ required: true }]}>
        <Input />
      </Form.Item>
      <Button type="primary" htmlType="submit" disabled={!isValid}>
        Submit
      </Button>
    </Form>
  );
}
```

### Modals with Forms

```tsx
function EditModal({ visible, onClose, dataset }: ModalProps) {
  const [form] = Form.useForm();
  const { mutateAsync: updateDataset, isPending } = useUpdateDataset();

  const handleSubmit = async (values: FormValues) => {
    await updateDataset({ id: dataset.id, ...values });
    message.success("Updated successfully");
    form.resetFields();
    onClose();
  };

  return (
    <Modal open={visible} onCancel={onClose} footer={null}>
      <Form form={form} onFinish={handleSubmit} initialValues={dataset}>
        {/* form fields */}
        <Button type="primary" htmlType="submit" loading={isPending}>
          Save
        </Button>
      </Form>
    </Modal>
  );
}
```

## Loading & Error States

### Consistent Pattern

```tsx
function MyComponent() {
  const { data, isLoading, error, refetch } = useMyData();

  if (isLoading) {
    return (
      <div className="flex min-h-[400px] items-center justify-center">
        <Spin size="large" />
      </div>
    );
  }

  if (error) {
    return (
      <Alert
        type="error"
        message="Failed to load data"
        description={error.message}
        action={<Button onClick={() => refetch()}>Retry</Button>}
      />
    );
  }

  if (!data || data.length === 0) {
    return <Empty description="No data found" />;
  }

  return <div>{/* render data */}</div>;
}
```

## Real-time Updates

**Use subscriptions for live status changes:**

```tsx
// In custom hook (src/hooks/useDatasetSubscription.ts pattern)
useEffect(() => {
  const channel = supabase
    .channel("dataset_updates")
    .on("postgres_changes", { event: "UPDATE", schema: "public", table: "v2_datasets" }, (payload) => {
      // Invalidate relevant queries
      queryClient.invalidateQueries(["datasets", payload.new.id]);
    })
    .subscribe();

  return () => {
    supabase.removeChannel(channel);
  };
}, []);
```

## Performance

### Memoization

```tsx
// Memoize expensive calculations
const processedData = useMemo(() => expensiveTransform(data), [data]);

// Memoize callbacks passed as props
const handleClick = useCallback(
  (id: number) => {
    /* ... */
  },
  [
    /* dependencies */
  ],
);
```

### Avoid Over-rendering

```tsx
// ✅ Store non-reactive data in refs
const mapRef = useRef<Map | null>(null);

// ❌ Don't store in state (causes re-renders)
const [map, setMap] = useState<Map | null>(null);
```

